Using the rule $(x, y) \to (-x, y)$:
$$
 A(1, 1) &\to A'(-1, 1) \\
 B(4, 1) &\to B'(-4, 1) \\
 C(2, 4) &\to C'(-2, 4)
$$

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 % Grid
 (-5,-1) grid (5,5);
 (-5,0) – (5.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-1) – (0,5.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Line of reflection
 (0,-1) – (0,5);

 % Original triangle
 ll[AtlasTeal!20] (1,1) – (4,1) – (2,4) – cycle;
 (1,1) – (4,1) – (2,4) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasTeal] (1,1) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,1) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (2,4) circle (3pt) node[above right] {$C$};

 % Image triangle
 ll[AtlasWarm!20] (-1,1) – (-4,1) – (-2,4) – cycle;
 (-1,1) – (-4,1) – (-2,4) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-1,1) circle (3pt) node[below left] {$A'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-4,1) circle (3pt) node[below left] {$B'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-2,4) circle (3pt) node[above left] {$C'$};
tikzpicture
center

Using the rule $(x, y) \to (-y, -x)$:
\[
 P(4, 1) \to P'(-1, -4)
\]

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.6]
 % Grid
 (-5,-5) grid (5,5);
 (-5,0) – (5.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-5) – (0,5.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Line y = -x
 (-5,5) – (5,-5);
 at (-4,4) {$y = -x$};

 % Original point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,1) circle (4pt);
 at (4,1) {$P(4, 1)$};

 % Image point
 ll[AtlasWarm] (-1,-4) circle (4pt);
 at (-1,-4) {$P'(-1, -4)$};

 % Connecting line
 (4,1) – (-1,-4);
tikzpicture
center

Using $(x, y) \to (x, 2k - y)$ with $k = 2$:
\[
 A(3, 7) \to A'(3, 2(2) - 7) = A'(3, 4 - 7) = A'(3, -3)
\]

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]
 % Grid
 (-1,-4) grid (6,8);
 (-1,0) – (6.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-4) – (0,8.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Line y = 2
 (-1,2) – (6,2);
 at (6,2) {$y = 2$};

 % Original point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (3,7) circle (4pt);
 at (3.2,7) {$A(3, 7)$};

 % Image point
 ll[AtlasWarm] (3,-3) circle (4pt);
 at (3.2,-3) {$A'(3, -3)$};

 % Connecting line
 (3,7) – (3,-3);

 % Distance markers
 at (3.5,4.5) {$5$};
 at (3.5,-0.5) {$5$};
tikzpicture
center

We can verify: $A$ is 5 units above the line $y = 2$, and $A'$ is 
5 units below it.

Apply the rule $(x, y) \to (x, 2(1) - y) = (x, 2 - y)$:
$$
 D(0, 4) &\to D'(0, 2 - 4) = D'(0, -2) \\
 E(3, 6) &\to E'(3, 2 - 6) = E'(3, -4) \\
 F(4, 2) &\to F'(4, 2 - 2) = F'(4, 0)
$$

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.55]
 % Grid
 (-1,-5) grid (6,7);
 (-1,0) – (6.5,0) node[right] {$x$};
 (0,-5) – (0,7.5) node[above] {$y$};

 % Line y = 1
 (-1,1) – (6,1);
 at (6,1) {$y = 1$};

 % Original triangle
 ll[AtlasTeal!20] (0,4) – (3,6) – (4,2) – cycle;
 (0,4) – (3,6) – (4,2) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,4) circle (3pt) node[left] {$D$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (3,6) circle (3pt) node[above] {$E$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (4,2) circle (3pt) node[right] {$F$};

 % Image triangle
 ll[AtlasWarm!20] (0,-2) – (3,-4) – (4,0) – cycle;
 (0,-2) – (3,-4) – (4,0) – cycle;
 ll[AtlasWarm] (0,-2) circle (3pt) node[left] {$D'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (3,-4) circle (3pt) node[below] {$E'$};
 ll[AtlasWarm] (4,0) circle (3pt) node[right] {$F'$};

 % Connecting lines
 (0,4) – (0,-2);
 (3,6) – (3,-4);
 (4,2) – (4,0);
tikzpicture
center
